This paper deals with the problem of noise-tolerant learning of classifiers, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically analyzes the noise-tolerance properties of risk minimization, which is a fundamental concept in machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
